New footage of a terrifying skydiving accident caused when two planes collided in mid-air shows the frantic split seconds as the jumpers scramble out of the plummeting wreckage.

The video is a jumper's eye-view from deep inside the Cessna aircraft during the dramatic crash 12,000ft above Superior, Wisconsin, last month.

It captures the screams of panic as the skydivers realise their aircraft is about to slam into the plane below them.

